tags: Policy3330(s1)
title: Policy3330(s1)(5)
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

When, in the judgment of the Superintendent of Schools or his/her designee, bid security is advisable, all bids must be accompanied by security in one of the following forms - certified check, cashier's check, personal money order, letter of credit or bid bond. The requirement for and the amount of the security must be set forth in the bid advertisement. All security presented must show the "Regional School District No. 8 Board of Education" as the payee.
